# Mapping Conventions

- Mapping must be explicit and file-per-entity.
- Application mappings handle `DTO <-> Domain`.
- Infrastructure persistence mappings handle `Domain <-> DatabaseEntity`.

# Rules

- Mapping classes must not contain I/O.
- Mapping classes must not depend on DI.
- Mapping classes must not contain business rules.
- Scalar copy operations must be explicit and readable.

# Naming

- Use consistent names such as `InstallationSiteMapping` and `InstallationSitePersistenceMapping`.
- Keep mapping methods symmetrical where appropriate, such as `ToDomain`, `ToDto`, `ToDb`, and `CopyScalars`.
